Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.60,0:01:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's programming rearrangement season.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.55,0:01:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A time of partings and new meetings.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.66,0:02:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We should hold each new meeting dear.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.71,0:02:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Cherish the fleeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.89,0:02:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Cherish the fleeting?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.71,0:02:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.52,0:02:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Each meeting must be treasured, because once gone, \Nmoments in time can never be reclaimed.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.37,0:02:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Said to be the words of the tea master, Sen-no-Rikyu.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:19.74,0:02:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming in!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:25.77,0:02:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.54,0:02:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.67,0:02:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Master said I could go on stage today.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.26,0:02:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Well, when I say stage, \Nwhat I {\i1}actually{\i0} mean is backstage!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.26,0:02:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I slay me!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.51,0:02:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I am oh, so, {\i1}so{\i0} delighted to meet you all!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.11,0:02:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, as they say in England, "One, please"! {Reference to Ichijo Marshmallow https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ve_XHlNS8H8}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.22,0:02:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, hottie alert!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.27,0:02:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You gots a BF?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.44,0:02:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How annoying.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.19,0:02:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is her problem?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.15,0:02:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}God, shut up!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.28,0:02:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really used to be a pot stirrer?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:53.74,0:02:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop with the on-air reporter shtick!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.36,0:02:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true you're divorced?{TM: I would end before Kigu's "eh?!".}{Agreed}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.83,0:03:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Do you wear gothic lolita clothes \N'cuz you think you look good in them?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.28,0:03:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't even with this jerkwad.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:04.25,0:03:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now. It's only for a day.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.87,0:03:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm here to shower you with love and support! {### gg's makes more sense here to me ("Nope, I'm a new supporting character")}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.96,0:03:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's the last episode! \NWe don't need your support!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.51,0:03:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She's late!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.06,0:03:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Today of all days?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.47,0:03:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I was hoping we could give \Nthe show a nice send-off!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.51,0:03:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Well, you know what they say. \NAll's well that ends well.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.43,0:03:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Hopefully it's just this once, \Nand we can let it all slide. {### here too ("this is our last time on screen, so let's just take it easy")}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.42,0:03:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.73,0:03:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's just this once.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.02,0:03:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! Cherish the fleeting!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.06,0:03:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you laugh or cry, it's the final episode!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.90,0:03:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We've gotta cherish this meeting!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.87,0:03:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Meeting you all today makes me...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.94,0:03:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, {\i1}so{\i0} grateful!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.36,0:03:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So annoying.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.49,0:03:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just this once! Just for today!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:39.87,0:03:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you even gonna tell us who you are?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:43.24,0:03:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Oh! Of course! Where are my manners?! \NLet me introduce myself!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.46,0:03:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we have a little name quiz?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.85,0:03:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wants to guess? C'mon now!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.12,0:03:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear to god, she's {\i1}so{\i0} annoying!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.07,0:03:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only one day!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.21,0:03:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I don't see any raised hands. \NYou'll make Ms. Me cry, pupils!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.04,0:04:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Okay then, let's make it so everyone \Ncan raise their hands!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.26,0:04:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If you have a good guess, \Nraise your hand like "paper",
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.16,0:04:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}if you kind of think you know, \Ngo with "scissors",
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.27,0:04:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}and if you have no idea, \Ngo with "rock". Got that?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.52,0:04:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this, parent's evening at school, Mr. Kinpachi?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.43,0:04:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,She's so damn annoying!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.44,0:04:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just this once...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.48,0:04:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Bzzzt, time's up!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.12,0:04:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just tell us your name already!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.48,0:04:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time for the big reveal!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.48,0:04:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.86,0:04:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Uzannu Uzattei!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.37,0:04:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget it, now!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.34,0:04:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She's so annoying!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.33,0:04:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just this once...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.45,0:04:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, "Voiced by ***ko Shin****".
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.54,0:04:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She's so annoying!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.56,0:04:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just this once!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.66,0:04:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What's everyone else's names, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.54,0:04:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm—
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.60,0:04:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, wait, wait, wait! Don't tell me yet, oh no!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.02,0:04:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She's {\i1}so{\i0} annoying!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.85,0:04:37.04,Alt,,0,0,0,,It's just this once.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.55,0:04:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what Rikyuu says...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.59,0:04:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,For most moments...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.01,0:04:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Once is enough!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.01,0:04:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget "cherish the fleeting".
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.01,0:04:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Nine out of ten times, \Nit's {\i1}good{\i0} that the moment is fleeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.77,0:04:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Lining up for hours at an attraction \Nbecause you don't know when you'll come again...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.61,0:04:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, once is enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.48,0:05:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Waiting outside a pancake place \Nbecause you happened to be in the area...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.28,0:05:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, once is enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.15,0:05:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That internet friend you've been emailing \Nfor a year who you finally got to meet...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.04,0:05:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, once is enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.89,0:05:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Once is enough!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.61,0:05:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That circus of the sun.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.86,0:05:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Rockers who sing on and on about the good old days.{TM: I would snap the start to the scene change to maintain symmetry.}{I think it will be jarrning since it will mess lead and very confusing with the pause}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.45,0:05:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The first or second qualifying round \Nof the World Cup.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.71,0:05:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Movies about a space probe \Nthat just went there and came back.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.85,0:05:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,American candy.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.55,0:05:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hollywood remakes.{TM: Snap start to scene change.}{Done}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.55,0:05:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Middle-school reunions.{TM: Snap start to scene change.}{Done}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.04,0:05:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Porn made by former celebrities.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.18,0:05:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Live action anime movies!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.38,0:05:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddammit! She's so annoying!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.14,0:05:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just one time.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.13,0:05:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But there are plenty of products \Nthat rely on once being enough!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.01,0:05:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Products that aren't so much \Nlimited edition as "once only",
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.08,0:05:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}where they clearly don't intend \Nfor people to come back.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.30,0:05:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Products where getting you to pay for it once is enough!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.73,0:05:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Meeting up once is enough for me!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.11,0:05:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Used cars.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.82,0:05:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Restaurants at tourist spots.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.16,0:05:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Expensive health goods.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.49,0:05:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Try them even once and \Nyou're playing right into their hands!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.03,0:05:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly right.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.08,0:05:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Once is enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.66,0:05:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she just change?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.52,0:05:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}All I need is one opportunity \Nto bring about your downfall.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.04,0:06:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I just noticed that Marii somehow \Nended up on the teasing side.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.72,0:06:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,She's usually the one being teased!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.87,0:06:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I just realised that her strawberry-patterned kimono \Nis kinda stealing my niche!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.43,0:06:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She's kinda stealing my niche!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.97,0:06:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, stop copying me!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.14,0:06:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, looks like I've upset the character balance.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.86,0:06:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's the last episode,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.31,0:06:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}it only takes one rogue element to ruin things \Nas thoroughly as you-know-who ruined Japan!{TM: End before the laugh.}{Done}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.11,0:06:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Time for stage two of your destruction.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.78,0:06:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Plastic explosives?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.99,0:06:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.76,0:06:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're infringing on {\i1}my{\i0} character!{TM: End before the laugh.}{Done}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.47,0:06:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Character balance: in shambles!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.62,0:06:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's true that there are characters who \Nruin the balance just by showing up once.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.08,0:06:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.17,0:06:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To send this show into an early grave.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.88,0:06:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The show was ending today anyway!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.84,0:06:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to Annoying Girl, airing next week!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.56,0:06:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What a bloody cheek!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.19,0:07:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't let you get away with this!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.19,0:07:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But the balance has been ruined so thoroughly...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.11,0:07:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I know a solution!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.28,0:07:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ex*le method.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.39,0:07:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If you add a whole load of new members, stuff like balance \Nor individual character goes out the window!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.91,0:07:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This many members is so annoying!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.77,0:07:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The annoyer has become the annoyee.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.75,0:07:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's breaking character!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.21,0:07:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll pay for this!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.88,0:07:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We won!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.93,0:07:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Once was definitely enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.96,0:07:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma, how was these nice ladies' rakugo?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.69,0:07:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, once was enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.84,0:07:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a taste of our own medicine.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.52,0:07:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Once was enough...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.43,0:07:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe kids just don't get traditional arts.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.43,0:07:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When she's older, she'll definitely...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.53,0:07:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Season two will be an annoying live-action adaptation!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.69,0:07:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Piss off!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.01,0:07:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Which way are we going?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.74,0:08:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it's this way.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.86,0:08:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Did we make a U-turn somewhere?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.45,0:08:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Think so.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.60,0:08:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, look.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.39,0:08:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Left, huh.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.51,0:08:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? I think we were right before.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.15,0:08:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.20,0:08:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.04,0:08:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.20,0:08:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't they want us to go down those stairs over there?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.79,0:08:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is needlessly confusing.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.50,0:08:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What? The signs for Electric Town disappeared!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.68,0:08:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just getting outside was a bit of a mission.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:57.37,0:09:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the legendary Akihabara Labyrinth.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.81,0:09:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They say that those who get lost in \Nits multi-level hell are never seen again.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:05.57,0:09:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}So {\i1}that's{\i0} why you didn't want \Nto come to a place like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.85,0:09:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, "a place like this"?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.59,0:09:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Akihabara is a world-famous tourist hotspot!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.24,0:09:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We're not just talking appliances, cameras, \Ncomputers, and high-end audio equipment.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.70,0:09:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We're talking hobby goods, \Nidol merch, games, and anime!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.69,0:09:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't underestimate the depth of Akihabara!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.65,0:09:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're very enthusiastic, Gan!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.29,0:09:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Like a fish that found water, \Nor a fan that found a meet-and-greet ticket.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.92,0:09:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I wouldn't have expected it. \NShe's a little obsessed, even.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.96,0:09:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Sounds like we should get Gan \Nto give us a little tour.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.03,0:09:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.35,0:09:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To the Rajikan!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.29,0:09:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The Magician?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.01,0:09:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}No, the Rajikan! That's the nickname \Nfor the Radio Kaikan!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.59,0:09:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You could say that the Radio Kaikan \Nis the beating heart of Akihabara!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.94,0:09:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The main building is being rebuilt, apparently.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.57,0:09:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't know that, Gankyou?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.53,0:09:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Oh, how the turns have tabled! \NWhat now, super fan?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.74,0:10:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}There are second and third locations \Nin addition to the main one...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.54,0:10:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she needs a rest.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.17,0:10:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She's being arrested!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.00,0:10:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Just questioned. It's common in Akiba.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.96,0:10:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you qualify, they'll stop you every fifty metres.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.92,0:10:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not qualifying, that's failing.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.52,0:10:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Apparently, they'll keep stopping you \Nif you're wearing a fanny pack.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.14,0:10:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.89,0:10:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I guess because you never know \Nwhat could be inside them.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.54,0:10:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Fanny packs contain nothing but hopes and dreams!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.44,0:10:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not suspicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.31,0:10:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Gan's back.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.81,0:10:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness I didn't have a knife.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.08,0:10:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a box cutter could be bad news these days.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.54,0:10:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does that leave manga artists?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.20,0:10:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How would they cut panels?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.51,0:10:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget anime creators!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.68,0:10:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How would they cut peg holes?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.45,0:10:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Do a lot of work in the streets of Akiba, do they?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.74,0:10:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is great! I love looking at household appliances.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.68,0:10:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They have a lot of niche products like electric \Ntempura machines, egg boilers, and waffle makers.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.44,0:10:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The best-sellers have got to be rice cookers.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.96,0:10:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Rice cookers?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.01,0:11:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}For some reason, foreign visitors \Nalways seem to buy three or four.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.20,0:11:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan leads the world in rice cooker technology.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.27,0:11:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The most expensive ones \Nthat fluff the rice up using a vacuum
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.87,0:11:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}or are lined with copper \Ncan easily set you back 100,000 yen.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.40,0:11:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}100,000 yen?! Do you really need to spend that much \Nto cook rice that costs two thousand yen for two kilos?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.49,0:11:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Depending on the shop, you might \Nbe able to get them a little cheaper...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.93,0:11:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what store is the king of Akiba?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.54,0:11:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently Laox is a luxury brand in China.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.54,0:11:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Luxury brand? It's just a regular shop.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.94,0:11:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I don't know which one is the top, \Nbut they all have one thing in common:
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.64,0:11:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Their theme songs are all earworms.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.34,0:11:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishimaru! Ishimaru!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.97,0:11:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow! Sato Wireless!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.85,0:11:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Onoden! La la la!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.52,0:11:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Laox!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.39,0:11:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Akiba means Yodobashi Camera!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.56,0:12:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This old bridge is very calming.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.96,0:12:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Akiba's a very frenetic kind of place. \NOne minute you're in, the next you're out.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.66,0:12:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Same goes for those theme songs we just sang. \NSome of them you just don't hear anymore.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.73,0:12:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Long-standing things like this bridge \Nare few and far between.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.75,0:12:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We haven't done anything yet \Nand I'm already drained.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.25,0:12:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,'Tis a strange old town, Akihabara.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.82,0:12:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}An army fights on its stomach. \NWanna go eat something?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.09,0:12:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We should eat something that screams "Akiba!"
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.51,0:12:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Like what?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.78,0:12:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hotpot in a can?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.05,0:12:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not that...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.61,0:12:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,These new kebab things?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.49,0:12:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not quite...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.57,0:12:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,An amateurish omelette and rice cooked by a maid?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.79,0:12:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}There's places where young women \Ntry their best to make sushi for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.00,0:12:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}There's a bar with an N-gauge model \Nrailway running through it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.71,0:12:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}And a café where voice actors speak \Nin lines appropriate to your order.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.42,0:13:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Also a drag king café.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.88,0:13:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm full now. Full of this nonsense!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.86,0:13:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't there any normal restaurants?!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.01,0:13:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh, Marii's gone aggro.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.59,0:13:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Akiba's a lovely place that's kind to visitors.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.08,0:13:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You're speaking up for it after \Nbeing questioned by the police?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.66,0:13:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This place has a legend.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.32,0:13:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}There once was a young man who \Nwas experiencing his first real crisis.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.17,0:13:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A herculean mission.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.30,0:13:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A wall that was insurmountable alone.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.29,0:13:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Then, help came through the internet \Nfrom the residents of Akiba.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.91,0:13:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean that Train Man?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.84,0:13:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I wonder if they'll ever distribute the royalties \Nfrom the book to the forum posters.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.54,0:13:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I smell an ulterior motive...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.00,0:13:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a pretty fancy place.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.19,0:13:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope we're not under-dressed...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.41,0:13:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine! It's just a restaurant.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.43,0:13:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Besides, if we were too fashionable, \Nit wouldn't feel like Akiba.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.27,0:13:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Don't worry. They have a space over there where \Nthey hold an event that is 100% pure-grade Akiba.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.90,0:14:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of event?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:00.58,0:14:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Basement Idol.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.74,0:14:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Heya, everybodies!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.82,0:14:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you hate me, don't hate Akiba!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.04,0:14:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I've got a song for you. It's called \N"Look Forward to Continued Annoyance".
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.48,0:14:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get outta here.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.69,0:14:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Hey, guys. Do you prefer mochi \Nsimmered in miso or clear soup?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.40,0:14:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask such dull questions!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.44,0:14:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The conversations in this anime \Nare written to be as inoffensive as possible
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.49,0:14:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}so as not to interfere with \Nyour enjoyment of viewing cute girls.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.30,0:14:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, that's it. I'm done. I can't eat anymore!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.17,0:15:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I'm pretty sure we cooked \Nevery kind of mochi imaginable.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.21,0:15:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we had more actual rice, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.84,0:15:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Check it out!{TM: I would end this at the scene change at 0:15:07.55 because the important part of the syllable has finished by the time the change happens.}{Agreed}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.51,0:15:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, rice?! How'd you get your hands on this?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:10.85,0:15:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I made it out of mochi!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.56,0:15:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you bake the mochi.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.39,0:15:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you chop it up into teeny, tiny pieces.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.69,0:15:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Then you simply put it in a rice bowl. \NAnd you're done! Ready to serve!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:22.07,0:15:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Woo, rice!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.65,0:15:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Just eat mochi like a normal person!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.56,0:15:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat it as-is without doing a bunch of weird things to it!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.42,0:15:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.11,0:15:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What Gan is trying to say is...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.74,0:15:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to read manga, read manga.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.12,0:15:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Adapting it into an anime makes no sense!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.69,0:15:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.59,0:15:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you saying?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.46,0:15:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why take a perfectly fine manga,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:44.03,0:15:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}where we do little more than talk in this room \Nday in, day out, and make an anime out of it?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.13,0:15:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more, enjoy a broadcast as a broadcast!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.09,0:15:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you ever burn them onto discs?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.66,0:16:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Why take a manga featuring conversations \Nthat don't require animation,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.31,0:16:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}turn it into an anime, broadcast it, and then \Nsell it on disc? Why jump through the hoops?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.47,0:16:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you wanted to say, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.78,0:16:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.07,0:16:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It may be unnecessary, but the hard-working studio staff \Nare working on a painstakingly fatal schedule
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.41,0:16:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}and going to a lot of trouble \Nto animate us in incredible detail!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.99,0:16:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a bit much, Gan.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.20,0:16:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't say that!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.54,0:16:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Dear God, please make it so Gan is shown \Nonly as rough sketches without any edits.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.00,0:16:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Put me back!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:21.21,0:16:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If you wanna play like that, \NI hope that at your future wedding banquet,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.92,0:16:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}all the dishes are melon with ham. \NStarters, mains: {\i1}All. Ham. Melon{\i0}.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.84,0:16:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanna eat melon as melon!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.51,0:16:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.03,0:16:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The bride never gets to eat anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.39,0:16:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it, Kigu.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.80,0:16:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Wouldn't you hate it if all the fruit you ever ate \Nfor the rest of your life had ham on it?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.85,0:16:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I just want to eat bananas and grapes and mandarins \Nand watermelon without anything extra!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.98,0:16:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you understand what I'm saying, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.07,0:16:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.52,0:16:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Gan's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.01,0:16:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been tricked by a con woman.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.61,0:16:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Anyway, what I'm {\i1}trying{\i0} to say is that you shouldn't add \Nweird elements or inflict bizarre arrangements on things!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.59,0:16:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It seems like adding extra elements \Nis a bit of a worldwide fad at the moment.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.54,0:17:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Add even a little, and you run the risk of people yelling \N"This ruins the original!" and "The new stuff blows!"
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.71,0:17:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They did their best with them, \Nbut were those B parts {\i1}really{\i0} necessary?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.16,0:17:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She says in the last episode!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.54,0:17:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Anyway, forget ranking extra elements. \NI'd say it's more like ranking how unnerving something is.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.73,0:17:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Take music, for example.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.97,0:17:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If you come to Japan and sing in Japanese, \Nit's J-pop, no matter who's singing!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.20,0:17:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mix in weird crap!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.09,0:17:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Don't say that. We can't afford \Nto have them cancel our sales!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.62,0:17:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You bespectacled nationalist!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.29,0:17:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I've found celebs with... extra elements.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.52,0:17:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There's definitely a little extra.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.90,0:17:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A little extra on top.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.15,0:17:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Definitely.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.15,0:17:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's more than a little extra. It's a whole pile!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.12,0:17:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Show your real selves!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:32.24,0:17:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a little too forceful...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.86,0:17:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look, a drama!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.72,0:17:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They turned this one into a film.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:37.59,0:17:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They also made it an anime. In Musashi-Sakai.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.26,0:17:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,TV is fine! Why make a movie or an anime?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.29,0:17:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's true that when a drama is turned into \N"Such-and-Such: the Movie",
Dialogue: 10,0:17:45.79,0:17:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}everything gets so big-budget that they lose \Nwhat made it special in the first place.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.55,0:17:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Yeah, like they'll introduce terrorist organisations \Nand serial killers and whatnot.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.30,0:17:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not kidding. Give me dramas as dramas only!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.48,0:18:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That's incorrect. A lot of dramas started as manga, \Nso you should say "Give me manga as manga!"
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.57,0:18:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}In other words, when it comes to spinoffs, \Nif the film was originally a drama,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.77,0:18:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}you should watch the drama, and if the drama \Nwas originally a manga, you should—
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.32,0:18:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as it's entertaining, who cares?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.13,0:18:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}So what if it's made into an anime, \Nand so what if they go on to sell that anime in stores?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.33,0:18:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as it's entertaining, who cares?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.78,0:18:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really laying on the pressure.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.91,0:18:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you put clothes on the dog?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.62,0:18:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just enjoy a dog as a dog!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.71,0:18:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Lots of people say that, \Nbut even dogs feel the cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.94,0:18:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The number one cause of \Ndoggy deaths in winter is the cold.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.51,0:18:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Plus, it's a good way to stop them \Nfrom shedding all over your house.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.44,0:18:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope. I like my dogs naked!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.30,0:18:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't give a woof.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.43,0:18:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs should be naked! Mutt naked!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.60,0:18:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who let you make those pawful jokes?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.39,0:18:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, the dog hated being nude after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.39,0:18:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}No, wait! Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.06,0:18:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I don't think it cared one way or another; \Nit just hated the "mutt naked" joke.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.98,0:18:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's just tough on puns.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.94,0:18:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.24,0:18:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Gah, dammit!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.36,0:18:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel very supported.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.84,0:18:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Fanservice in the very last episode?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.04,0:19:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pull out all the stops in the final episode.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.70,0:19:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's true!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.70,0:19:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A naked woman... No,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.47,0:19:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"La Megane"!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.64,0:19:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"La Megane"? What is that, French?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.19,0:19:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.21,0:19:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Bespectacled Birthday Suit?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.80,0:19:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Babies aren't born with glasses on.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:13.67,0:19:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This won't do, Gan!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.72,0:19:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What won't?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.63,0:19:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Use a washbasin as a washbasin!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.01,0:19:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't rearrange it as a cover for your private parts!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.99,0:19:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't a rearrangement, it's an emergency situation!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.94,0:19:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If we may.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.02,0:19:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That washbasin is made of metal, is it not?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.25,0:19:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Please {\i1}donate{\i0} it.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:31.40,0:19:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why on earth do you need it?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.74,0:19:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She said it's to make Ospreys.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.24,0:19:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Use a washbasin as a washbasin! We're not at war!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.34,0:19:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}How are we going to help our brave lads on the home front \Nif you won't give up a simple washbasin?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.62,0:19:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's going on out there.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.91,0:19:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like the world's gone to hell.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.67,0:19:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I say to make America mad at us?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.88,0:19:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you angered America.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.14,0:20:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about these ladies, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.92,0:20:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take this metal and use it for the greater good!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.52,0:20:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That's what you get for \Nsubstituting clothes with a washbasin.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:08.93,0:20:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The Women's Association weren't monsters. \NThey left this for you to wear.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.98,0:20:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My beautiful prince!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:18.41,0:20:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not worthy to stand in your presence, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.98,0:20:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So manly and cool!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.55,0:20:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I'm a woman! Treat women as women! \NDon't add any extra elements!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.95,0:20:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.62,0:20:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up, Marii?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.12,0:20:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I'm the one who's suspected of \Nbeing a cross-dressing boy!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.45,0:20:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She's infringing on my character!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.92,0:20:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Treat a cross-dressing boy as a cross-dressing boy!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.46,0:20:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Marii just come out to us?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:38.63,0:20:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.65,0:20:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It was true!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.71,0:20:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}N-No! It's not about my gender, \Nit's about my character!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.57,0:20:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Treat Marii as Marii!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.19,0:20:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.78,0:20:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither man...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.46,0:20:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor woman...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.55,0:21:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the indefinable Marii.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.70,0:21:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with the soppy tone?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:02.62,0:21:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this how you're gonna end the last episode?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.92,0:21:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Marii, you're on next.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.37,0:21:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.33,0:21:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.63,0:21:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to take to the stage.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.66,0:21:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"The world's full of people shoutin' and groanin', \N'The end is nigh! It's all over!'"
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.36,0:21:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"But the scariest end has gotta be \Nthe end of life, don't ya think?"
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.75,0:22:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"But then again, that's the only kind of endin' \Nwhich comes to everybody, without discrimination."
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.68,0:22:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"So I reckon the only thing ta do is to just keep on \Nlaughin' and smilin' right until the very end."
